<subSubSection box="[199,1251,873,899]" pageId="10" pageNumber="254" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1151]" box="[199,1251,873,899]" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,873,899]" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin, “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera" authorityYear="2020" box="[535,639,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriosus">
<emphasis box="[535,639,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">gloriosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, referring to the attractive appearance of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="254" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1151]" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,908,935]" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera, 2020" authorityName="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera" authorityYear="2020" box="[339,545,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[339,545,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">Bubaces gloriosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[552,649,909,935]" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[552,643,909,935]" pageId="10" pageNumber="254" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
is included in the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[868,978,910,935]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis box="[868,978,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” group because its total length is greater than 
<quantity box="[206,309,945,971]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="10" pageNumber="254" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.70 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1151]" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicName authority="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera, 2020" authorityName="Brailovsky &amp; Barrera" authorityYear="2020" box="[199,407,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,407,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">Bubaces gloriosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[416,506,981,1007]" pageId="10" pageNumber="254" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is segregated by having the dorsal surfaces of the pronotum, clavi and coria glabrous, each corium has a circular yellow to creamy-yellow subapical spot, the head has a shallow ventral longitudinal sulcus, and the rostrum reaches the posterior border of abdominal sternite IV or sometimes to the middle third of V. In 
<emphasis box="[212,376,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brailovsky" authorityYear="1981" box="[212,372,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convergens">B. convergens</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the must similar species, the dorsal surfaces of pronotum, clavi and coria are clothed with fine erect and longer hairs, and each corium lacks a circular yellow, to creamy yellow subapical spot.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
